orary global context and how they face the challenge of balancing socio-economic integration and cultural distinction. It uncovers the conflicts of tourism development between a poor community, tourists, governments and brokers. This micro study has ramifications beyond the locality. Many other villages in Indonesia are experiencing similar issues. Many of the challenges are relevant to peripheral communities across the globe. Themes in this book will resonate with studies of tourism, tourists, development, globalisation and cultural change from around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jul 2020) 0aEconomic developmentxIndonesiaxNgada. 0aEconomic developmentzIndonesiazNgada. 0aTourismxSocial aspectsxIndonesiaxNgada. 0aTourismxSocial aspectszIndonesiazNgada. 4aIndonesia. 4aethnography. 4aplanning. 4apro-poor tourism. 4aremote communities. 4atourism development. 4atourism stakeholders. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184541071140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845410711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781845410711.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK